This paper deals with graph embedding models that incorporate textual information, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on improving the efficiency of training objectives and utilizing text information, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on link prediction tasks, which are common in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
